{
  "text": "The first group includes 39 cyclic alkanes, such as n-alkylcyclohexanes (C 11 -C 26 ), nalkylcyclopentanes (C 12 -C 26 ), 2-alkyl-1,1,3-trimethylcyclohexanes (C 11 and C 13 ), and methyland dimethyldecalins (Figs. 5a, b , and c). Absolute or relative concentrations of this group started increasing at the depth of the sediment 83102 (upper part of the Kusanagi Formation), maximised at the sediment 90103 (middle part of the Kusanagi Formation), and then decreased in the bottom two sediments. Similar depth profiles were observed with n-alkanes (C 15 -C 38 ), pristane plus phytane (Fig. 5d) , and the reported EOC/TOC ratio ( Fig.  5e ; [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
